Without an explicit CORS policy, browser-based cross-origin requests are uncontrolled. Define it explicitly:

```js
const cors = require('cors');

app.use(cors({
  origin: process.env.ALLOWED_ORIGIN || 'https://yourdomain.com',
  methods: ['GET'],
  allowedHeaders: ['Content-Type', 'Authorization'],
}));
```

